It is clear from the form of the classical solution that there is no
anomalous dimension for the fundamental field , whereas the
expression  shows that there would be anomalous dimensions for
composite operators in general. The first term in  is the
contribution of free field theory. Thus the second term may be used to
define a dimensional running  coupling constant
(p) = 1 + 2d^dk (2)^d 1(p-k)^2 k^2   
The basic integral is given by
